$MODULE
DIOCO_DOC_ID: lc_example_my-course_01-greetings
TITLE: Greetings and Introductions
DESCRIPTION: Learn basic greetings and how to introduce yourself
TARGET_LANG_G: fr
HOME_LANG_G: en
VOICE_DEFAULT: Aoede
VOICE: Narrator | Narrator | Fenrir | Speak slowly and clearly
VOICE: Marie | Marie | Kore | Young French woman, friendly tone
VOICE: Pierre | Pierre | Achernar | Middle-aged French man

$LESSON Greetings

$DIALOGUE Meeting Someone
INTRO: Listen to Marie and Pierre meeting for the first time.
INSTRUCTION: Pay attention to the formal greetings used.

SPEAKER: Marie
VOCAB: Bonjour
VOCAB_T: Hello / Good day
LINE: Bonjour, je m'appelle Marie.
LINE_T: Hello, my name is Marie.

SPEAKER: Pierre
LINE: Bonjour Marie. Je m'appelle Pierre. Comment allez-vous ?
LINE_T: Hello Marie. My name is Pierre. How are you?
NOTES: "Comment allez-vous" is the formal way to ask "how are you"

SPEAKER: Marie
VOCAB: très bien
VOCAB_T: very well
LINE: Je vais très bien, merci. Et vous ?
LINE_T: I'm doing very well, thank you. And you?

$EXERCISE Practice Greetings
INSTRUCTION: Complete the responses using what you learned.

EXAMPLE
PROMPT: Hello, my name is Marie.
PROMPT_T: (Introduce yourself)
RESPONSE: Bonjour, je m'appelle Marie.
RESPONSE_T: Hello, my name is Marie.

PROMPT: How are you? (formal)
RESPONSE: Comment allez-vous ?
RESPONSE_T: How are you?

PROMPT: I'm doing very well, thank you.
RESPONSE: Je vais très bien, merci.

$GRAMMAR Formal vs Informal

## Tu vs Vous

French has two words for "you":

- **Tu** — informal, used with friends, family, children
- **Vous** — formal, used with strangers, elders, in professional settings

| French | English | Register |
|--------|---------|----------|
| Comment allez-vous ? | How are you? | Formal |
| Comment vas-tu ? | How are you? | Informal |
| Ça va ? | How's it going? | Very informal |

When in doubt, use **vous**. It's always polite.

$LESSON Farewells

$DIALOGUE Saying Goodbye
INTRO: Marie and Pierre say goodbye after their conversation.

SPEAKER: Pierre
LINE: Au revoir, Marie. Bonne journée !
LINE_T: Goodbye, Marie. Have a good day!

SPEAKER: Marie
LINE: Au revoir, Pierre. À bientôt !
LINE_T: Goodbye, Pierre. See you soon!

